text:
WHO Regional Director for Europe stated that the "Older people are at highest risk from COVID-19, but all must act to prevent community spread". The worldwide COVID-19 patient report suggested that old age people have more chances to infect as compared to youngster .
According to the available reports from federal centers for disease control in China, approximately 80 % of died patients are more than 60 years old. However, in Italy, it was ~ 81 years old (Aronson et al., 2020) . It has been reported that one-third of died American patients are about 65 years old. In Italy, higher fatality rate (~ 20 %) has been reported for older (< 80 years) patients;
however, China has ~ 14 % for the same (Grasselli et al., 2020) . Elderly people are more likely to experience a condition of acute respiratory failure, an acute lung infection that causes many deaths (Gerst et al., 2015) . However, it also appears that the virus is more likely to damage the heart, and people may die from heart attacks with COVID-19 (WHO Team et al., 2020).
